Reasoning: The paper proposes a novel framework for encoding time series as images and using computer vision techniques for time series classification and imputation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning models such as tiled CNNs and DAs suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the use of imputation techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
